      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "OAKLEY SHARD NZ (4) progressed off a fresh placing for a strong win at this circuit and distance last time, racing up to four wide but still managing to get home by 4 metres. Peaking now and has come from wider in both outings this time in. The lower draw can see her strike again. CAPTAIN NEMO NZ (2) is another that will appreciate a good draw having come from wider barriers of late but he has been going well from out there, winning three back at this circuit and distance and placing over further last week. EDWARD JAY (3) returns to a mobile start and draws well. Has won third up before so can peak. STUDLEIGH MARK (1) was only beaten 4.6m last time and recorded a series of placings prior. Should every chance from the inside draw.",
